nguage.This volume offers the first translation into English, thereby making the work available to a wider audience; it is accompanied by a detailed commentary on its historical, religious, military, architectural and political elements, elucidating the narrative fully. The volume also contains a contextual introduction, considering what can be known of the author, and the manuscript tradition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aMedieval German Literature. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aArmenia.  aCairo.  aCatholicism.  aCologne.  aEgypt.  aGeorgia.  aIslam.  aJudaism.  aMamluk Sultanate.  aPersia.  abotany.  anobility.  aornithology.  atravelogue.  avernacular.1 aClassen, Albrecht, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805433033?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805433033423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805433033/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles